ARG is normally the prefix argument for the calling command.
ITEMS should be a list of item names."
  (let ((count (length items)))
    (if (= count 1)
        (car items)
      ;; more than 1 item:
      (if (integerp arg)
          (format "[%s %d items]" (if (> arg 0) "next" "previous") count)
